<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1893,2028]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,420,1893,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Taxonomical remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Seyrig" authorityYear="1927" box="[428,709,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Pseudocymodusa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancilla">
<emphasis box="[428,709,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Pseudocymodusa ancilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holmgren" authorityYear="1859" box="[903,1021,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,1021,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Aubert, J. - F." box="[1064,1218,1893,1920]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="133 - 166" refId="ref5638" refString="Aubert, J. - F. (1959) Les Ichneumonides du rivage mediterraneen francais (Cote d'Azur) (Hym.). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 127, 133 - 166." type="journal article" year="1959">Aubert (1959</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Aubert, J. - F." box="[1230,1290,1893,1919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="847 - 878" refId="ref5677" refString="Aubert, J. - F. (1963) Les Ichneumonides du rivage Mediterraneen francais (5 e serie, Department du Var). Vie et Milieu, 14, 847 - 878." type="journal article" year="1963">1963</bibRefCitation>
); later it was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smits van Burgst" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[364,587,1929,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[364,587,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the same author (
<bibRefCitation author="Aubert, J. - F." box="[823,970,1929,1955]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="27 - 70" refId="ref5713" refString="Aubert, J. - F. (1969) Deuxieme travail sur les Ichneumonides de Corse (Hymenoptera). Veroffentlichungen der Zoologischen Staatssammlung Munchen, 13, 27 - 70." type="journal article" year="1969">Aubert 1969</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Dbar, R. S." box="[990,1128,1929,1956]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="588 - 600" refId="ref5921" refString="Dbar, R. S. (1985) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Cymodusa Holmgren (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). II. Entomologicheskoye Obozreniye, 64, 588 - 600. (in Russian)" type="journal article" year="1985">Dbar (1985)</bibRefCitation>
agreed with Aubert’s treatment in his revision, he also considered 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seyrig" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[620,826,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancilla">
<emphasis box="[620,826,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa ancilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smits van Burgst" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1203,1429,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[1203,1429,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="272">Cymodusa australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Horstmann, K." box="[267,473,2001,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="272" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref6266" refString="Horstmann, K. (1992) Typenverzeichnis der von A. Seyrig beschriebenen westpalaarktischen Ichneumonidae, mit einer Revision der Campopleginae. Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen, 41 (2), 56 - 62." type="journal article" year="1992">Horstmann (1992)</bibRefCitation>
removed it from synonymy, without any argument to support its valid specific status. Several years later 
<bibRefCitation author="Horstmann, K." box="[371,580,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="113 - 126" refId="ref6339" refString="Horstmann, K. (2013) Revisionen von Schlupfwespen-Arten XVII (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Mitteilungen der Munchen- er Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 103, 113 - 126." type="journal article" year="2013">Horstmann (2013)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out some minor differences to distinguish 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seyrig" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[1167,1373,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancilla">
<emphasis box="[1167,1373,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa ancilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smits van Burgst" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[151,374,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[151,374,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, this comparison was only applicable for males. Based on the present examination of large samples (100+ specimens), the extremely minor differences given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Horstmann, K." box="[1003,1210,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="113 - 126" refId="ref6339" refString="Horstmann, K. (2013) Revisionen von Schlupfwespen-Arten XVII (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae). Mitteilungen der Munchen- er Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 103, 113 - 126." type="journal article" year="2013">Horstmann (2013)</bibRefCitation>
were not consistent either for males or for females. The main character to separate the females of these species was considered the absent median section of the anterior transverse carina in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seyrig" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[768,972,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancilla">
<emphasis box="[768,972,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa ancilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the careful examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">holotype</typeStatus>
female specimen of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seyrig" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[482,686,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancilla">
<emphasis box="[482,686,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa ancilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that 
<bibRefCitation author="Seyrig, A." box="[843,998,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="235 - 240" refId="ref6788" refString="Seyrig, A. (1927) Travaux scientifiques de l'Armee d'Orient (1916 - 1918). Hymenopteres Ichneumonides. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 33, 235 - 240." type="journal article" year="1927">Seyrig (1927)</bibRefCitation>
wrongly stated that the median section of the anterior transverse carina is absent and area basalis and area superomedia are not separated in the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen. The median section of the anterior transverse carina is clearly present in the 
<typeStatus box="[1115,1216,403,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">holotype</typeStatus>
, only slightly lower than the adjacent longitudinal carinae, therefore area basalis and area superomedia are distinctly separated. [It is worth to note that 
<bibRefCitation author="Seyrig, A." box="[354,508,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="235 - 240" refId="ref6788" refString="Seyrig, A. (1927) Travaux scientifiques de l'Armee d'Orient (1916 - 1918). Hymenopteres Ichneumonides. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 33, 235 - 240." type="journal article" year="1927">Seyrig (1927)</bibRefCitation>
also failed to recognise the otherwise present pilosity of the eyes, as pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Aubert, J. - F." box="[151,318,510,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="133 - 166" refId="ref5638" refString="Aubert, J. - F. (1959) Les Ichneumonides du rivage mediterraneen francais (Cote d'Azur) (Hym.). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 127, 133 - 166." type="journal article" year="1959">Aubert (1959)</bibRefCitation>
.] Since it turned out that the median section of anterior transverse carina is present in the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,511,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seyrig" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[183,388,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancilla">
<emphasis box="[183,388,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa ancilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, similarly to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smits van Burgst" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[541,766,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[541,766,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and no other reliable and consistent morphological difference were found to distinguish these species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seyrig" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[660,863,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancilla">
<emphasis box="[660,863,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa ancilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered again a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smits van Burgst" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[151,374,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[151,374,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="273" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,654,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smits van Burgst" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[331,556,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Cymodusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[331,556,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Cymodusa australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits considerable intraspecific variability in size and colouration of legs (however, on a morphological basis it was not possible to delimit reliably distinguishable subgroups due to the overlapping character states). Females of the species can be distinguished from the other Palaearctic species of the “australis” species group (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Dbar, R. S." box="[521,670,762,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" pagination="588 - 600" refId="ref5921" refString="Dbar, R. S. (1985) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Cymodusa Holmgren (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae). II. Entomologicheskoye Obozreniye, 64, 588 - 600. (in Russian)" type="journal article" year="1985">Dbar (1985))</bibRefCitation>
by the following. Ovipositor sheath 0.8–0.9× as long as hind tibia. Propodeal carination as in 
<figureCitation box="[448,547,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,395,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-103@3.[151,1436,381,1853]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Morphological details of Cymodusa species. 1–5, Cymodusa irata sp. nov.; 1, habitus (holotype); 2, head, female; 3, areolet; 4, propodeum; 5, head, male; 6, Cymodusa nigra Šedivý, propodeum; 7–8, Cymodusa australis (Smits van Burgst), propodeum, variations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810176/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="273">Figs 7–8</figureCitation>
; note that costulae are often obsolescent distally but proximally always discernible, area superomedia is never conspicuously elongate, and area petiolaris is always wide. Nervellus intercepted by the spectral discoidella. Tegula yellowish, metasoma black, second and often third tergites with posterior margins reddish, hind femur orange to dark brownish, hind tibia orange to brownish, basally with a paler spot (which is variably distinct but always discernible), subbasally and apically more or less darkened. The identification of males is often difficult, only the typical males can be identified reliably, since the males of some, more or less similar species are unknown, and males lack several important specific characters of females such as convergence of eyes and ovipositor length. Body length ca. 
<quantity box="[539,677,1050,1077]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="4.5">4.5–7.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
